&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;context&#34;&gt;Context&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Distinguishable&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;Repeatable&lt;/em&gt; biometric references can be extracted from speech, such as, x-vectors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advances in Speech synthesis, Voice cloning [1] and Speaker recognition pose severe privacy threat.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An &lt;strong&gt;attacker&lt;/strong&gt; tries to reveal the identity of the speaker in a public dataset.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The attacker has access to some &amp;ldquo;found data&amp;rdquo; and &amp;ldquo;knowledge&amp;rdquo; of anonymization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;contributions&#34;&gt;Contributions&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
Compare anonymization using 3 voice conversion methods.
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
Design 3 attackers based on their &amp;ldquo;knowledge&amp;rdquo; of anonymization:

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ignorant&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Semi-Informed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Informed
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
Evaluation of &lt;span style=&#34;color: #EF7A7A&#34;&gt;privacy&lt;/span&gt; and &lt;span style=&#34;color: #EF7A7A&#34;&gt;utility&lt;/span&gt;.
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

