&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;evaluation-protocol&#34;&gt;Evaluation protocol&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attackers are simulated using speaker verification, which produce PLDA scores.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color: #EF7A7A&#34;&gt;PLDA scores&lt;/span&gt; = log-likelihood ratio between &lt;em&gt;same-speaker&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;different-speaker&lt;/em&gt; hypotheses.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Equal Error Rate (&lt;span style=&#34;color: #31B404&#34;&gt;EER&lt;/span&gt;) is computed using PLDA scores.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Higher EER indicates &lt;span style=&#34;color: #EF7A7A&#34;&gt;high privacy&lt;/span&gt;; Lower EER indicates &lt;span style=&#34;color: #EF7A7A&#34;&gt;low privacy&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utility of anonymized speech is quantified using Word Error Rate (&lt;span style=&#34;color: #31B404&#34;&gt;WER&lt;/span&gt;).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h1 id=&#34;results&#34;&gt;Results&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&#34;results-on-privacy-eer&#34;&gt;Results on privacy (EER)&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;font-size: 20pt&#34;&gt;As the knowledge of attacker increases, &lt;span style=&#34;color: #EF7A7A&#34;&gt;privacy&lt;/span&gt; (EER) decreases.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;width: 10em; height: 10em&#34;&gt; 
  &lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
   &lt;img src=&#34;/img/eer_bars_baseline.svg&#34; style=&#34;border: none; position: absolute&#34; /&gt;  
&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
   &lt;img src=&#34;/img/eer_bars_ig.svg&#34; style=&#34;border: none; position: absolute&#34; /&gt;  
&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
   &lt;img src=&#34;/img/eer_bars_si.svg&#34; style=&#34;border: none; position: absolute&#34; /&gt;  
&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
   &lt;img src=&#34;/img/eer_bars_in.svg&#34; style=&#34;border: none; position: absolute&#34; /&gt;  
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;plda-score-distribution&#34;&gt;PLDA score distribution&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;More overlap between the score distribution ensures more privacy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Overlap decreases as we move from &lt;em&gt;Ignorant&lt;/em&gt; to &lt;em&gt;Informed&lt;/em&gt; attacker.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;height: 10em;&#34;&gt; 
  &lt;img src=&#34;/img/score_dist.svg&#34; style=&#34;border: none; width: 40em&#34; /&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&#34;results-on-utility-wer&#34;&gt;Results on utility (WER)&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;font-size: 20pt&#34;&gt;
- With rise in WER, utility decreases for all VC algorithms. &lt;br /&gt;
- VoiceMask and VTLN produce reasonable loss of utility.
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div style=&#34;height: 10em;&#34;&gt; 
  &lt;img src=&#34;/img/wer_bars.svg&#34; style=&#34;border: none;&#34; /&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&#34;conclusion&#34;&gt;Conclusion&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Investigated VC algorithms for speaker anonymization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We show that &lt;span style=&#34;color: #31B404&#34;&gt;target selection&lt;/span&gt; and &lt;span style=&#34;color: #31B404&#34;&gt;attacker&amp;rsquo;s knowledge&lt;/span&gt; are critical for strength of anonymization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Simple methods can provide reasonable protection.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&#34;future-directions&#34;&gt;Future directions&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Search for speaker anonymization which produces &lt;span style=&#34;color: #EF7A7A&#34;&gt;high EER&lt;/span&gt;, even in &lt;em&gt;Informed&lt;/em&gt; attack scenario.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Explore cross-gender anonnymization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyse the PLDA scores using other metrics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

